 "howto.goal": "Goal: Help Sahelia reach its five national milestones (one per UN 2.0 strategy) while keeping Trust above the collapse line, before your term ends across four Acts.",
 "howto.s1": "Briefing and Event: A field story sets the scene, then the world acts, with a shock, an opening, or a hard choice.",
 "howto.s2": "Your turn: Spend Capacity to play Action cards. Each advances a pillar, shifts Trust, or builds resources. Partnership cards super-charge your next matching action. Use your role's ability once per month.",
 "howto.s3": "Resolution: Crises cost Trust until resolved. Fill a pillar to 100% to complete a Milestone.",
 "howto.res": "Resources: Trust (the meta-currency), Funding, Coordination, Data, and Capacity.",
 "howto.strat": "The five strategies (Quintet of Change): Data, Digital, Innovation, Foresight, Behavioural Science. Balance them; hoarding one is never optimal.",
 "howto.tiers": "Win tiers: bronze avoids collapse; silver reaches three milestones; gold reaches all five with high trust.",
 "credits.intro": "Common Ground: a strategic card game about UN field coordination, built for the UN 2.0 Quintet of Change.",
 "credits.l1": "Design and code: Common Ground project.",
 "credits.l2": "Music and sound: original, procedurally synthesised in-browser (Web Audio API), royalty-free.",
 "credits.l3": "Art: CSS, SVG and system emoji. No external assets.",
 "credits.l4": "Setting: Sahelia is fictional and composite. Any resemblance to a real nation is coincidental.",
 "credits.l5": "Optional AI narration: Anthropic Messages API (claude-sonnet-4-6), only if you supply your own key.",
 "tut.0.title": "Welcome, Coordinator",
 "tut.0.body": "You are the Resident Coordinator in Sahelia. You have no command authority; your power is to align people, data, and resources. Let's learn by doing.",
 "tut.1.title": "Trust is everything",
 "tut.1.body": "Watch the Trust meter at the top. It gates your biggest moves. If it hits zero, your term ends. Build it with community visits, dialogue, and honesty.",
 "tut.2.title": "The five strategies",
 "tut.2.body": "Each national milestone maps to one UN 2.0 strategy: Data, Digital, Innovation, Foresight, Behavioural Science. Fill a pillar to 100% to complete its milestone. Balance all five.",
 "tut.3.title": "Play, then react",
 "tut.3.body": "Spend Capacity to play Action cards. Use your role's ability once a month. The world throws shocks and openings; coordinate under pressure. Ready?",
